ZH: 他是个迷信的人，经常拜佛求神保佑。
EN: He is superstitious, often praying to Buddha for protection.

ZH: 她不敢打破镜子，因为她相信这会带来七年的厄运。
EN: She dares not break a mirror, because she believes it will bring seven years of bad luck.

ZH: 有些人迷信地认为黑猫会带来不幸。
EN: Some people superstitiously believe that black cats bring misfortune.

ZH: 星座信仰被视为一种迷信，但很多人还是会关注它。
EN: Belief in astrology is considered superstition, but many people still pay attention to it.

ZH: 他完全相信风水的影响，经常调整家里的摆设。
EN: He completely believes in the influence of feng shui, and often adjusts the layout of his home.

ZH: 他坚持要穿红色内衣来保护自己免受邪恶的影响。
EN: He insists on wearing red underwear to protect himself from evil influences.

ZH: 她相信摆放一对金鱼可以带来好运。
EN: She believes that having a pair of goldfish can bring good luck.

ZH: 许多人在买房子前会请风水师看看风水是否合理。
EN: Many people consult a feng shui master before buying a house to ensure the layout is auspicious.

ZH: 孩子们每天早上都会在门口画符符，以保佑平安。
EN: The children draw symbols at the door every morning to ensure safety and peace.

ZH: 他害怕穿绿色衣服，因为在他的文化中绿色象征着倒霉。
EN: He is afraid to wear green clothes because in his culture, green symbolizes bad luck.

ZH: 过年时，我们家会放鞭炮，以驱逐邪灵。
EN: During Chinese New Year, we set off firecrackers to drive away evil spirits.

ZH: 有些人相信夜晚吹笛子会招鬼，从而避免在夜晚吹口哨。
EN: Some people believe that playing a flute at night attracts ghosts, so they avoid whistling at night.

ZH: 在很多地区，如果你踩到别人丢的拖鞋，就要抬起脚将之踢出去以避免厄运。
EN: In many regions, if you step on someone else's lost slipper, you should lift your foot and kick it away to avoid bad luck.

ZH: 我们古代祖先相信太阳和月亮在天空中的运动会影响人类的命运。
EN: Our ancient ancestors believed that the movement of the sun and moon in the sky would affect human destiny.

ZH: 据说在拆迁时要保护门神，以免招惹祸端。
EN: It is said that the door god should be protected during demolition to avoid trouble.

ZH: 民间传说中有许多与吉凶有关的迷信传统。
EN: There are many superstitions and traditions related to good and bad luck in folklore.

ZH: 她一定要在马上吃荔枝，因为她认为这会给她带来好运。
EN: She must eat lychee immediately, as she believes it will bring her good luck.

ZH: 在西方文化中，将雨伞打开室内被认为带来厄运。
EN: In Western culture, it is believed that opening an umbrella indoors brings bad luck.

ZH: 在传统皇室仪式中，穿着黄色有可能具有追随天意的象征意义。
EN: Wearing yellow in traditional royal ceremonies may have symbolic significance in following the will of heaven.
